cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL, cs.HC 

The paper is about developing and validating a deep learning system to detect abnormalities on chest X-rays, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the system on radiology workflows and public health screenings, which could also be relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
